-1 MULTIPLAYING MULTI-PLAYING~
Expansion on the Multiplaying rule `##`33``

Multiplaying, and helping your own alts on AnimeMUD is `!H`1i`!GHLY``   
illegal, and will get you slain, deleted, banned, or worse depending
on how it's done, how often it's done etc. To be on the safe side, play
your character, and all of your alts like you didn't own the others.
Don't try and help them in ANY, we mean ANY, way. Violations of this
rule include, but are not limited to:

1) The actual act of multiplaying; Logging in more than one
character, from the same or different sites. Even if you don't
interact the characters with eachother, it's still illegal and
you will lose your equipment for it.

2) Giving EQ to your alts through any means. This includes:
Dropping EQ on the ground and logging in your alt to grab it.
Giving EQ to a mobile and logging in an alt to kill the mobile
and take it. Giving EQ to a friend to give to your alt when you
log him in. Logging in one alt, going linkdead, and logging in
another alt and walking/gating/etc. to your linkdead character
to give it Equipment. Or anyother means devised to transfer EQ
from one character you own to another character you own. This
means any object, including GOLD. Also type HELP `8'`#SHARING`8'`` for
info on shared characters.

3) Helping out characters you own with other characters you own,
this includes; Spelling up your alts by going linkdead, or multi
-playing to bring two of your alts online and aid them with spells
of any type, this includes summoning and protective spells such
as sanctuary and armor. Helping level your own alts, by means of
weakening, or dispelling mobiles so you can login your alt
and kill the mobiles easier. This also includes grabbing your  
corpse with an alt and giving it back to your character who
died.

If you need further clarification, note to immortal and ask for
clarification on whatever aspect of this rule you want to know
about.
~

-1 SHARING SHARED CHARACTERS SHARED-CHARACTERS~
Sharing characters in the realm of AnimeMUD is tolerated, but
not looked highly upon. While it's legal to share a character,
it brings up some problems with the multiplaying rule. To make
it simple, shared characters are treated like everyone who has
access to that character's alt. This means that the shared char
*IS* your alt, even if someone else also plays him, and any
interaction with your other alts from the shared character will
be treated as a violation of the multiplaying rule. This means
shared alts can not give you equipment, spell-ups, aid leveling
when the other owner is playing that character and you are playing
another one of your alts. For example: John and Jane both own the
character Sharey, John can not login Sharey and help out Jane,
because Jone also owns Sharey, and likewise for John.

If this is the least bit confusing, just follow this guideline:
If you have access to a shared character, do not interact with
that shared character with any of your alts. Do not use that  
shared character to help out any of the other owner's alts.   

`4-`` I`&M``M Staff
~

